<p>R has the function <code>outer</code> that allows you to compute a function for every combination of inputs <code>xs</code> and <code>ys</code>, e.g.:</p>  <pre><code>xs &lt;- 1:5 ys &lt;- 0:10 zs &lt;- outer(xs, ys, Vectorize(function(x, y) sin(x) + y**2)) </code></pre>  <p>Let's say I want to know the minimal value in <code>zs</code>:</p>  <pre><code>&gt; min(zs) [1] -0.9589243 </code></pre>  <p>and what position it's in:</p>  <pre><code>&gt; which(zs==min(zs)) [1] 5 </code></pre>  <p>Now how can I figure out which x of <code>xs</code> and which y of <code>ys</code> produced the 5th z of <code>zs</code>?</p>  <p>I can recompute using something like <code>outer(xs, ys, Vectorize(function(x, y) paste(x,y)))[which(zs==min(zs))]</code> to get a string of the indices, but this seems bloody inefficient to me. What's a better way?</p>